Two people were shot dead in a hail of bullets on the N2 northbound between Gingindlovu and Mandeni, KwaZulu-Natal, on Wednesday night. IPSS Medical Rescues paramedics said a car, with three people inside, had been traveling towards Gingindlovu when another vehicle allegedly pulled alongside it, and opened fire with high calibre rifles. IPSS said the people in the car that was under attack tried to escape the hail of bullets but two of them were shot dead. The third person was critically injured and was taken to hospital. IPSS said the motive for the shooting was unknown.